  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some great online resources for learning the Go (Golang) programming language?",
  "response": "Learning Go (Golang) has become increasingly popular due to its simplicity, efficiency, and performance. There are many excellent online resources available for beginners and experienced programmers alike. Here are some of the best:\n\n---\n\n### **Interactive Tutorials and Courses**\n1. **The Go Programming Language (Official Tour)**  \n   - [https://go.dev/tour/](https://go.dev/tour/)  \n   - An interactive tour provided by the Go team. Great for beginners to learn syntax and core concepts.\n\n2. **Codecademy: Learn Go**  \n   - [https://www.codecademy.com/learn/learn-go](https://www.codecademy.com/learn/learn-go)  \n   - A beginner-friendly course with hands-on exercises.\n\n3. **Exercism: Go Track**  \n   - [https://exercism.org/tracks/go](https://exercism.org/tracks/go)  \n   - Practice Go by solving coding challenges and getting feedback from mentors.\n\n4. **Udemy: Go (Golang): The Complete Bootcamp**  \n   - [https://www.udemy.com/course/learn-go-the-complete-bootcamp-course-golang/](https://www.udemy.com/course/learn-go-the-complete-bootcamp-course-golang/)  \n   - A comprehensive course for mastering Go.\n\n---\n\n### **Books and Documentation**\n1. **\"The Go Programming Language\" by Alan A. A. Donovan and Brian W. Kernighan**  \n   - A highly recommended book for learning Go, available on platforms like Amazon.\n\n2. **Effective Go (Official Documentation)**  \n   - [https://go.dev/doc/effective_go](https://go.dev/doc/effective_go)  \n   - A guide to writing idiomatic Go code.\n\n3. **Go by Example**  \n   - [https://gobyexample.com/](https://gobyexample.com/)  \n   - A hands-on approach to learning Go with practical examples.\n\n---\n\n### **Video Tutorials**\n1. **The Net Ninja: Go Tutorials**  \n   - [https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL4cUxeGkcC9gC88BEo9czgyS72A3doDeM](https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL4cUxeGkcC9gC88BEo9czgyS72A3doDeM)  \n   - A beginner-friendly YouTube playlist.\n\n2. **Tech With Tim: Go Tutorials**  \n   - [https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLzMcBGfZo4-mtY_SE3HuzQJzuj4VlUG0q](https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLzMcBGfZo4-mtY_SE3HuzQJzuj4VlUG0q)  \n   - A practical and engaging YouTube series.\n\n3. **Gophercises**  \n   - [https://courses.calhoun.io/courses/cor_gophercises](https://courses.calhoun.io/courses/cor_gophercises)  \n   - A collection of coding exercises with video explanations.\n\n---\n\n### **Communities and Blogs**\n1. **Gopher Slack**  \n   - [https://invite.slack.golangbridge.org/](https://invite.slack.golangbridge.org/)  \n   - Join the Go community on Slack to ask questions and learn from others.\n\n2. **The Go Blog**  \n   - [https://go.dev/blog/](https://go.dev/blog/)  \n   - Official blog with articles on best practices, updates, and use cases.\n\n3. **Gopher Academy Blog**  \n   - [https://blog.gopheracademy.com/](https://blog.gopheracademy.com/)  \n   - A community-driven blog with tutorials and insights.\n\n---\n\n### **Practice Platforms**\n1. **LeetCode: Go Problems**  \n   - [https://leetcode.com/](https://leetcode.com/)  \n   - Solve coding problems using Go to improve your skills.\n\n2. **Codewars: Go Challenges**  \n   - [https://www.codewars.com/](https://www.codewars.com/)  \n   - A gamified platform for learning Go through challenges.\n\n---\n\n### **Advanced Topics**\n1. **Concurrency in Go**  \n   - [https://go.dev/doc/effective_go#concurrency](https://go.dev/doc/effective_go#concurrency)  \n   - Learn about goroutines, channels, and concurrency patterns.\n\n2. **Go Patterns**  \n   - [https://github.com/tmrts/go-patterns](https://github.com/tmrts/go-patterns)  \n   - A curated collection of Go design patterns.\n\n3. **Building Web Applications with Go**  \n   - [https://gowebexamples.com/](https://gowebexamples.com/)  \n   - Examples and tutorials for building web applications.\n\n---\n\nThese resources should provide a solid foundation for learning Go (Golang) and advancing your skills. Happy coding! \ud83d\ude80",
  "temperature": 1.0,
